<CSSEmpty-cells>
<summary>
The <strong><c>empty-cells</c></strong> CSS property sets whether borders and backgrounds appear around <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/table">table</see> cells that have no visible content.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/css/empty-cells.html")</para><para>This property has an effect only when the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-collapse">border-collapse</see> property is <c>separate</c>.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-collapse">border-collapse</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/CSS/Building_blocks/Styling_tables">Styling tables</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/empty-cells"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</CSSEmpty-cells>
